
[1]indifferently

   INDIF'FERENTLY, adv. Without distinction or preference; as, to offer
   pardon indifferently to all.

   1. Equally; impartially; without favor, prejudice or bias.

   --They may truly and indifferently minister justice.

   2. In a neutral state; without concern; without wish or aversion.

   Set honor in one eye and death i'th' other,

   And I will look on death indifferently.

   3. Not well; tolerably; passably; as indifferently well; to be
   indifferently entertained.
